# Hybridcloud — Core Rules

## Non-Negotiable Constraints

- **No secrets in Git.** Use Vault + ExternalSecret/PushSecret only.
- **Never delete `sovereign-*` namespaces.** Tenant-managed; add resources only.
- **GitOps only after bootstrap.** After `make init-central-argo`, all changes via ArgoCD.
- **`oc` is for investigation only.** No `oc apply` for configuration changes post-bootstrap.

## Operator Architecture

- **Primary operator** (`operator/primary/`): watches `sovereign-cloud` for Entity CRs and `sovereign-cloud-plugins` for plugin config CRs.
- **Namespace operators** (`operator/namespace/`): one Deployment per `entity-*` namespace; watches tenant CRs only in that namespace.
- **No global singleton** reconciling all entity namespaces.

## Deployment

- OCI charts: `oci://quay.example.com/hybrid-sovereign/<chart>`
- Bump chart versions and update `bootstrap/helm/central/values.yaml` after every chart change.
- Every feature must have a spec in `specs/`.
